Theory 2:
On the site you gave us (http://opensource.ebswift.com/RaspiMonitor/wensn/), there was this function (dB = (byte1 + ((byte2 & 3) * 256)) * 0.1 + 30) that made me think that maybe the 2nd byte is actually not the timeoffset but the 2nd byte for the dB.
This makes dB Float instead of Integer which would make much more sense. Also the output I got from the 2nd theory felt much better so I assume this is the correct answer.
<pre><code>#define _CRT_SECURE_NO_WARNINGS
#include <Windows.h>
#include <string>
